Shanghai Plans to Offer Rewards For Leads on Food Violations

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-26T02:56:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/shanghai-plans-to-offer-rewards-for-leads-on-food-violations.html
Shanghai  plans to offer rewards of
at least 500 yuan for information about food-safety violations,
Shanghai  Food and Drug Administration  said in a statement posted
on its website on Sept. 23.  The government agency is seeking public opinion on the
plan, according to the statement.  Rewards may be increased for those who provide information
on major food-safety cases, according to the draft plan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 swong139@bloomberg.net  